<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,1545,2041]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,340,1581,1608]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Type series.</emphasis>
The original description refers to a single male specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1066,1130,1583,1609]" name="Japan" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Japan</collectingCountry>
given for description to E. Reitter by K. M. Heller from MTD. In coll. Faust (
<collectionCode box="[711,778,1618,1644]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4j3t-w40g" name="Museum of Zoology Senckenberg Dresden" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">MTD</collectionCode>
), there is a well-preserved, 
<quantity box="[1082,1182,1618,1645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.76" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="4.76">4.76 mm</quantity>
long specimen labeled “typus! / 
<collectingCountry box="[259,323,1655,1681]" name="Japan" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Japan</collectingCountry>
...[illegible] / Coll. J. Faust Ankauf 1900 / Staatl. Museum für Tierkunde Dresden / 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter M. Kostal et R. Caldara" authorityYear="1904" box="[1293,1406,1654,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cionus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">C. Helleri</taxonomicName>
m Type–1904,”. We remounted this specimen, dissected its genitalia and realized that it is a female. For clarity, we provided this specimen with a label “ 
<typeStatus box="[558,728,1726,1752]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">HOLOTYPUS</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Reitter M. Kostal et R. Caldara" authorityName="Reitter M. Kostal et R. Caldara" authorityYear="1904" box="[733,1232,1726,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cionus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">Cionus helleri Reitter M.Košťál et R.Caldara</taxonomicName>
vid. 2017 [printed red label]”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,1545,2041]" box="[199,404,1797,1825]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
